                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I use NBG in almost every group I am in. The example that you used in your second example is flawed. In the situation of an ornate drop I am pretty sure that ther eis no way to know which ornate mold/pattern will drop. In other words you went to BoT with a group not to camp a specific piece but to exp in BoT. Therefore everyone shared the hope fo getting a drop. If the leather would have dropped instead of the silk then the Necro wouldn't have ever had a chance at the loot. In your first example you use a camp such as FT3 Boots in CT. This too is flawed. Next to the Swirling Red Mass camp is the mosquito camp. Usually both mobs are camped at the same time. So there would be an item for the melees. <br /><br />I am not here to shoot you down in your hypothesis on NBG. But your examples are flawed. There are problems with NBG. Tis too easy to switch out your gear if an item comes up to say that it would be an upgrade, or that only needed clases can roll even if it si not an upgrade... there are many scenarioes that fault NBG. However, choose the loot system before the group starts out and explain it to anyone joining subsequently thereafter. If there are disagreements then they will be identified early on. <br /><br />If you dont like NBG then just dont use it.<br /><br />Lue/Khris/Llemus<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
